Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for violating the term and order of payment of goods (works, services) in carrying out purchases for state and municipal needs.
This law is intended to solve the very acute problem of non-fulfillment of its obligations by customers in the implementation of state and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation when entrepreneurs could not get paid under state and municipal contracts was ubiquitous.
At the same time, the Russian President instructed the Prosecutor General's Office to of the Russian Federation to take the problem under special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers, who concluded unfunded contracts, tried in every way to evade the assumed obligations on payment and included in the contracts illegal conditions.
The problem was the system in the whole country.
Since 2015, in the interests of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the prosecutor's office has made 9.7 thousand submissions, according to the results of their consideration, 4.5 thousand officials have been brought to disciplinary responsibility, to the administrative - 533, to the investigative bodies for the organisation of procedural inspections 75 materials are presented, 46 of them are initiated criminal cases.
As a result, the debt owed to entrepreneurs amounted to more than 66 billion rubles.
And these huge sums have accumulated far not as a result of non-payment of multibillion-dollar contracts.
There have been numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs much more modest amounts.
Here is a typical case.
The head of a small company won a competition for services on social transport for several million rubles.
The man invested all his working capital, fully fulfilled the obligations, but put money in the time did not receive.
The result is a growing financial entity from wages, taxes,, which would lead to bankruptcy, if the entrepreneur did not apply for assistance from the prosecutor's office.
Now, in a number of regions, the problem has been solved as much as possible.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt on state and municipal contracts, revealed by prosecutors of subjects of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where the debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor's office works in a manual anti-crisis management.
The Attorney General personally conducts visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, where all the violations revealed by prosecutors and measures for their immediate elimination are in.
Such operational meetings have already been held in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg this year.
The implementation of the Federal Law № 189-FZ "On amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences in terms of establishing administrative responsibility of the customer's officials customer for violation of the term and order of payment of goods (works, services) in procurement for state and municipal needs," which was signed last week by the President of Russia.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Prosecutor General's Office.
The new law will complement the Code of Administrative Offences of the Russian Federation, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand to 50 thousand rubles for violation by an official of the customer of the term and order of payment for goods, works and services in the state and municipal procurement.
And if an official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he will be disqualified for a period of one year to two years.
All prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation have already received instructions to ensure the application of these legislative innovations in practice.
