Tyumen prosecutor's office is fighting with the HIV-dissident
The prosecutor's office challenged the decision of the Kaliningrad District Court of Tyumen, which stopped the criminal case against a local resident, who died from HIV a young daughter.
According to the investigation, the child died because the mother is HIV dissident and refused treatment.
However, the court relieved her of responsibility in connection with the reconciliation with the injured father.
The prosecutor's office believes that the crime can not be left unpunished, so as not to create a precedent for other HIV dissidents.
The case against a resident of Tyumen was initiated under Part 1 of Article 109 of the Criminal Code (causing death by negligence) in April - after the HIV infection 4V stage died her three-year-old daughter.
According to prosecutors, the mother herself is HIV-infected.
"The woman was not treated herself and refused to treat the daughter, believing that HIV infection does not exist," - explained in the prosecutor's office of the Tyumen region.
The criminal case was brought to the Kalinin district court Kaliningrad District Court of Tyumen, which on July 25 decided to stop it.
The petition was filed by the father of the deceased girl, explaining that "he forgave his wife, she has no claims against her, she took the harm and apologized."
The prosecutor's office with the decision of the court did not agree and filed an appeal, demanding to cancel the decision on termination of the case and send it to new consideration.
The girl died, and the harm caused by the crime is impossible.
The HIV-infected mother, contrary to the recommendations of the doctors refused to examine the baby and treat her from a dangerous infection, "- reported in the press service of the prosecutor's office.
According to the supervisory authority, it should be punished, otherwise its example will be followed by other HIV dissidents.
As told in the Tyumen AIDS Center, now in the Tyumen region about 12 children, HIV patients, do not receive medical care because of parents' refusal.
"And this situation has already improved - in the year of the work of the special group, half of parents who categorically refused to treat children from HIV, changed their opinion - allowed the diagnosis, began to take drugs," said a spokeswoman for the AIDS Centre, Elena Loseev.
According to her, the legislative way to act on parents is impossible, and as a result not all HIV-infected children are able to detect - mothers do not give them to, hide, run away with children from hospitals.
What are the dangers of HIV dissidents?
At the end of last year, St. Petersburg sociologists presented the results of the first study of the so-called movement of HIV dissidents in Russia.
HIV dissidents call people who deny the existence of HIV and refuse to take medication.
Medics and activists of AIDS service NGOs call such views anti-medical, and in their distribution see a serious threat.
