"In Libya, we don't want to be associated with any side of the conflict"
The authorities of the Russian Federation have lately noticeably stepped up their policy on the Libyan direction, and with visits to Moscow, delegations of opposing Libyan parties have.
The head of the Russian contact group on intra-Libyan settlement under the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation and the State Duma, the assistant to the head of the Chechen republic Lev Dengov told Kommersant, what goals are being pursued Moscow in the region and who makes a bet.
The contact group on Libya you lead, almost nothing is known.
Here, say, a contact group on Ukraine - everyone knows about it.
And here is the veil of mystery.
What exactly are you doing, what goals are being pursued?
The Contact Group was created on the initiative of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation and the State Duma.
Its activity is supervised by Deputy Foreign Minister Mikhail Bogdanov and Adam Delimkhanov (deputy of the Duma from Chechnya. - "Kommersant,").
The latter is authorized to work in the Libyan direction by Speaker of the State Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
The for the creation of the group was the detention in Libya of the Russian tanker "Mechanic Chebobáv" (in September 2015, there were 11 people on board). - "Kommersant.
We thought about how to help the crew.
Then the contact group of military specialists, representatives of the State Duma, was created, our work was supported by the head of Chechnya, Ramzan Kadyrov.
And it turned out, what exactly do you lead it?
Since I have been working on Libya since 2008, I have been asked to lead the group's work.
Our activity was not limited to the release of seafarers from the "Chebotarev Mechanics."
We managed to establish contacts with representatives of all the main factions opposing each other in the Libyan conflict - and on the part of Tripoli (where the UN-recognized government, led by Fazom Sarajem, is based), and with Tobruk (the of parliament, which opposes the government and supports Marshal Khalifa Haftar, who controls the eastern parts of Libya).
Thanks to the active participation of Ahmed Metiga (Deputy Prime Minister of Libya - Kommersant), we managed to quickly negotiate the release of Russian sailors.
Then it was decided to use these contacts more effectively, to create a contact group.
Its task is analysis of the situation, identify key factors and players, dialogue with all parties to the conflict.
I want to emphasize that in Libya we don't want to be associated with any side of the conflict, we are in dialogue with everyone.
How many people are in the contact group and how many of them are permanently in Libya?
Now the contact group includes five people.
Among them there are people with experience in the law enforcement agencies, including the Ministry of Defence.
We also want to introduce a group of specialists in the region, representatives of the Institute of the Middle East of the Russian Academy of Sciences.
No one is permanently in Libya.
There are now in Libya Russian military advisers, instructors.
And if so, on whose side?
There are no Russian military specialists in Libya.
All conversations and publications about it are not true.
But in your contact group, the former military enters...
Yes, and their presence is necessary.
For example, when we visit hot spots.
Or closed up to a certain point for us cities like Misuata (where the played a role in the overthrow of Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011 and in the. - Kommersant)).
We arrived in Misurata in January of this year.
We were frightened, they said that all of them are Islamists, terrorists.
But it was important for us to assess the situation there, to analyze the real military potential, who is responsible for what, why there are such rumors, what the role of Islamists is in reality.
In Misrata, we met with all the representatives of the detachments who were engaged in the destruction of ISIS in Sirte (in December 2016, this city on the Mediterranean coast was cut off from the militants banned in Russia "Islamic State" - "Kommersant").
We wanted to see them, get acquainted with these people, check the information that they played a decisive role in the destruction of ISIS in Libya, and not Khalifa Haftar, who attributed to himself these merits.
And to what conclusion did you come?
"Islamic State" in Libya won not Haftar?
It wasn't him.
Haftar conducted operations on another front, in Benghazi.
And with ISIS in Sirte the structures subordinated to the government in Tripoli were fought.
And, by the way, we invited people who carried out this anti-terrorist operation to Russia.
And they arrived - the visit lasted from 19 to 23 April this year, the Libyan delegation accepted in the Federation Council, in the Duma, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Rosguard.
You, as we have understood, are in all Libyan regions and probably imagine the mood of local elites and field commanders.
How do you think it will be possible to implement the ceasefire agreements, and the elections reached at the end of July in Paris by Khalifa Haftar and Faziz Saraj?
Or again, as has happened repeatedly in the past, the agreements will be sorted, the fighting will resume, the parties will try to sole seize power alone?
For us, the fact that Saraj and Haftar had agreed to another meeting, it was a good signal.
In the recent past, both leaders have been extremely negative about each other.
As for Russia's position...
Often write and say that Moscow actively supporting Haftar, many believe it.
We faced this situation when we were in, and Haftar was on the board of the Russian carrier "Admiral Kuznetsov" on this day.
It was a coincidence.
But in Misurat did not believe in the coincidence.
We were told: "you are probably very courageous people that came to us today."
But our task is just to show: we do not support only Haftar, we are in dialogue with all the key participants in the conflict in Libya.
You with Haftar communicated.
The understanding with Russian partners on a human, emotional level, the fact that he twice studied in the USSR?
And, by the way, does Haftar know the Russian language?
The Russian, if he knows, it is very relative.
But what he has learned, of course, facilitates dialogue with him.
And by the way not only with him.
When we communicate with the military in Tripoli and Misrata, we meet the generals who have studied either in Russia or in the Soviet Union.
And that's how they speak fluent Russian.
And they are drawn to Russia, to some extent feel nostalgic on it.
Do you consider the imminent cancellation of the arms embargo imposed on Libya?
Are your Libyan interlocutors interested in supplying Russian weapons?
We are interested, of course, but, as I have already said, we do not engage in this conflict and would not want to arm some to the detriment of others.
We would like everyone to be roughly equal.
As for the weapons embargo, there are frequent calls from Libyans to ensure that Russia has somehow contributed to its removal.
The process of drafting a constitution is now being actively pursued in Libya.
We hope that the parties will reach compromise solutions, and achieve internal consensus.
Then the elections are to be held, as well as discussed at the meeting between Saraj and Haftar.
If the elections are held and the legitimate government is finally elected (and now none of the parties have such a status), it is possible to put in the UN Security Council the issue of lifting the weapons embargo.
Raising this issue is now meaningless and dangerous, it will only lead to an escalation of the conflict.
