The factory, which produces, among other products, cookies Hobnobs and Rich Tea, employs more than 500 people.
The company Pladis, owner of the McVitie's, reports that over the past few years has invested in the facility more than 5 million pounds.
The company adds that in case of any changes in the work of the facility employees and representatives of the trade union will learn about them first.
In a letter to the head of the facility owned by the company, the Scottish branch of GMB demanded McVitie's reaction to the concern that the funding would not be allowed to upgrade production lines.
Senior organiser Drew Daffy said: "members of our trade union are deeply concerned that we cannot achieve clarity from the general manager of the facility on business and investment plan for the future of.
Families have worked here for generations, and the concentration of workers is great in local society and in the territory of Greater Glasgow; it is the most important pillar of decent work on the territory of high unemployment and social deprivation.
Thus, in terms of jobs, wages, and prosperity, and against the backdrop of Brexit, the growth of the living wage, and the chronic decline in production, Eastend Glasgow desperately needs the prosperity of production at McVitie's factory.
According to the representative of the company Pladis, head of the facility just yesterday received a letter from the Scottish branch of the GMB, and the company will respond immediately, as we value our ongoing cooperation with employees and union representatives ».
Two months ago, we held a regular meeting with the employees and representatives of the GMB, which openly discussed a number of issues.
We talked to employees about the fact that as all companies operating in the most competitive and unstable economic climate, we are constantly reviewing our actions and this applies to all our facilities and activities to remain competitive.
Over the past years, we have invested more than 5 million pounds in our colon facility, especially in production lines and improved functional performance. "
We are fully aware of the value of Tolkross as a production facility, and in case of any change in the work at this facility, employees and representatives of the trade union will learn about it first.
