Ukraine offered to send Russians to prison for illegal border crossing
In the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine registered a draft law, according to which in the republic may appear criminal penalties for Russians for illegal crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, the document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament envisages a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a second offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment can be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained on the border with the, the time of detention for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who tried to get to Russia outside established checkpoints.
