In Russia there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "" and "Novotroitsk."
The relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The borders and types of economic activity of the Torah on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakasia are defined.
The city, where 15 thousand people live, will have a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments into the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of types of economic activity under which a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will be in "," for example, includes crop production, animal husbandry, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already now the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory from the town-forming enterprise of the "Abakai mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development to create the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region also acted.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk will also be created a of ahead of social and economic development.
This will diversify the economy of monotowns, reduce its dependence on the town-forming enterprise JSC "Ural Steel," as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities, under which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will operate, are, in particular, freshwater fish farming, feed production, pharmaceuticals and medical supplies.
Novotroitsk became the first of the-industry towns of the Orenburg region, which received the status of TOR.
We remind that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR are the following: a profit tax of no more than 5% for the first five years, and no less than 10% over the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% over 10 years, the use of the free customs zone, a preferential treatment of to various infrastructure objects, and preferential rental rates.
